Defendant in custody. 
Probation has been revoked effective 09-14-2018. The defendant is now before the court for sentencing.
On both counts the Court sentences the defendant to thirty-two (32) months initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent to each other but consecutive to Milwaukee County case 15CF2182. 
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)	Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2)	Defendant is not to leave his county of residence without the agents approval;
3)	Defendant is to have no contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent, except for his immediate family;
4)	No use or possession of the internet or internet enabled devices without approval and no use of social media websites and all passwords are to be turned over to the agent;
5)	Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
7)	Pay court costs; 
8)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination.
Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Defendant is to be given 710 days sentence credit.
Minutes.

The State files an Amended Information which charges 1 count of solicitation of prostitutes and 1 count pandering, contrary to Section 944.32 and 944.33(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.
GUILTY pleas entered to both counts in the Amended Information.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety;
2) Defendant is not to leave his county of residence without the agents approval;
3) Defendant is to have no contact with the victim, her family, her residence or any temporary residence she occupies.  Defendant is to have no contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent, except for his immediately family;
4) No use or possession of the internet or internet enabled devices without approval and no use of any social media websites and all passwords are to be turned over to the agent;
5) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
6) Pay court costs of $798.00;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) spend one (1) year in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, commencing on 08-18-15 by 6:00 p.m.  Court authorizes transfer to Milwaukee County Jail.  No electronic monitoring is allowed;
9) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
10) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence in count 1.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
$798.00 of cash bail applied to court costs.  $202.00 balance is returned to Janice Perry by check instruction no: CR 84.
The defendant has credit for 97 days if revoked.
Minutes.

Stipulation and Order to Modify Bail Conditions.
It is ordered that the condition of bail requiring the defendant to report to the Manitowoc County Sheriff's Department by 3:00 p.m. every Sunday and Monday is eliminated;
The condition of bail prohibiting the defendant from traveling outside of the counties of Waukesha, Ozaukee, Manitowoc, Milwaukee, Racine, Kenosha, Washington and Sheboygan is modified to the defendant is prohibited from traveling outside of Milwaukee County for any purpose other than to attend schedule court hearings in Manitowoc County for Manitowoc County case no: 14 CF 197;
The condition of bail prohibiting the defendant from having no unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18 is modified to the defendant is to have no contact with anyone under the age of 18, with the exception of relative E.S., 10-28-2009 and A.S., 12-12-2006, unless the child's parent or legal guardian is present.
Copy of Stipulation and Order delivered to jail.
